<TITLE> Hasina mourns Maksuda Rafiq </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 10 (bdnews24.com)--Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has condoled the death of Maksuda Rafiq, the wife of Ershad Mohammed Rafiq. Maksuda was a sister-in-law of Sheikh Kamal, Sheikh Hasina's brother and eldest son of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. Hasina spent sometime among the relatives at their Sahjahanpur residence on Tuesday to mourn the death. Maksuda, 56, had been suffering from kidney diseases and some other difficulties since long. She was kept alive for three days on artificial life support at the LabAid Hospital. Her cousin Asifuzzaman told bdnews24.com the life support was removed early on Monday. She will be buried at the Matuail central graveyard on Tuesday afternoon. The first Namaz-e-Janaza of Kamal was held at the front yard of her residence. State minister for land Rezaul Karim Hira, state minister for law Kamrul Islam, BNP joint secretary general Mirza Abbas, relatives and local elite joined the prayer. bdnew
